Hackers completely cut transmission of 11 channels belonging to Paris-based TV5 Monde and took over its websites and social media accounts for a full three hours this morning . 
  The channel's director said the network has restored its signal but can only broadcast recorded programs . 
  Hackers posted documents on Facebook purporting to be identity cards of French soldiers involved in anti-ISIS operation in Iraq . 
  They also made threats against French troops . 
 